ch_hihouml_cardinal_ver01:data:sn83025121:00294552303:1907121701:0172/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83025121/1907-12-17/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.331948, "shard": "06", "shelf_id": "sn83025121, 1907-12-17, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/hihouml", "subject": ["newspapers", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "united states"], "subject_headings": ["Honolulu (Hawaii)--Newspapers", "Hawaii--Honolulu", "United States--Hawaii--Honolulu--Honolulu"], "subjects": [{"hawaii": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:hawaii&fo=json"}, {"honolulu": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:honolulu&fo=json"}, {"honolulu (hawaii)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:honolulu+%28hawaii%29&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2022-11-21T17:39:46.007Z", "title": "The Hawaiian gazette (Honolulu [Oahu, Hawaii]), December 17, 1907", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83025121/1907-12-17/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/sn83025121", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83025121/", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/b53ada29-4b14-5f3f-aead-7bf3051a30da"], "batch": ["hihouml_azure_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1865", "description": ["Semiweekly, Jan. 1894-<Oct. 18, 1918> Vol. 1, no. 1 (Jan. 21, 1865)- Ceased Nov. 29, 1918. Publishers: J. Mott-Smith, 1865-<1869>; M. Raplee, <1870-1872>; Henry M. Whitney, 1873-1878. Editors: 1866-1869, J. Mott-Smith; 1873-1877, H.M. Whitney; 1877, C.T. Rodgers; many others. Issues for <Jan. 7, 1874-Jan. 4, 1895> called also: whole no. <469-1616> Some issues accompanied by supplements. Also issued on microfilm from the Hawaiian Historical Society, and the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Archived issues are available in digital format as part of the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:24:58.411Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "catalog-split-07", "catalog", "ndnp/newspapers", "main-catalog-split-07", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83025121/", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [21.30992, -157.858158], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-157.858158, 21.30992], "number": ["new york pub libr res libr", "microfilm master", "online resource", "center for res libr, newsp proj", "1", "microfilm service copy", "library of congress", "boston pub libr", "new york hist soc, newsp proj", "hawaiian state arch", "american antiquarian soc, newsp proj", "new york state - lii", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83025121/1918-10-18/ed-1/", "2025-09-17t10:50:11.200000", "wisconsin hist soc, newsp proj", "original", "sn83025121", "kansas state hist soc, newsp proj", "huntington libr art gallery & gardens", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn83025121/1868-04-22/ed-1/", "9249554", "sn85047142", "3763", "2157-1392", "2020-07-02t10:33:22.014556", "hawaiian hist soc", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["catalog", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "the hawaiian gazette (honolulu [oahu, hawaii]) 1865-1918", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["semiweekly"], "score": 41.265408, "shelf_id": "Newspaper AN", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "catalog", "usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "electronic journals", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:05:22.105Z", "title": "The Hawaiian gazette.", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn83025121/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220158/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1880", "dates": ["[1880 TO 1885]"], "description": ["Weekly Print began with Volume I, Number 1 (September 4, 1880); ceased with Volume 5, Number 52 = whol enumber 261 (August 29, 1885). Supplements accompany many issues. Volume I, Number 1 (September 4, 1880); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 23, 2021). Volume 5, Number 52 = whole number 261 (August 29, 1885) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 23, 2021). Daily Honolulu press 2767-276X (DLC) 2021220159 (OCoLC)904427830"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:13.555Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220158/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["online resource", "2767-2786", "2021220158", "2021220159", "701514961", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "saturday press (honolulu, h.i.) 1880-1885 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "Saturday press", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220158/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220226/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1882", "dates": ["[1882 TO 1895]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.) Print began with No. 1 (Feb. 1, 1882); print ceased with Vol. IX, No. 1337 [i.e. 1340] (May 15, 1895). Issues for 1882-Dec. 19, 1891 called also v. 1-15; Dec. 21, 1891-1895, called v. 2-9. Has semimonthly supplements, 1888, called: Daily bulletin summary; has weekly supplements, 1889-May 15, 1895, called: Weekly bulletin summary (varies). No. 1 (February 1, 1882); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). Vol. IX, No. 1337 [i.e. 1340] (May 15, 1895) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). Evening bulletin (Honolulu, Hawaii) 2767-8628 (DLC) 2021220227 (OCoLC)904430143"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:12.813Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220226/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["2021220226", "online resource", "2021220227", "2767-8636", "701512295", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["J.W. Robertson's daily bulletin"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the daily bulletin (honolulu [hawaii]) 1882-1895 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD Internet Access AEU", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "periodicals", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "electronic journals", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "The Daily bulletin", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220226/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220227/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1895", "dates": ["[1895 TO 1912]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sunday) Print began with Vol. 1 No. 1 (May 16, 1895); ceased with No. 5,276 (June 29, 1912). Issued also on Sunday, Jan. 26-Apr. 1902, as: Sunday bulletin. Editors: June 17, 1895-June 10, 1898, D. Logan; June 13, 1898-1912, W.R. Farrington. Vol. 1 No. 1 (May 16, 1895); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). No. 5,267 (June 29, 1912) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). Hawaiian star 2771-0688 (DLC) 2021220559 (OCoLC)904431854 Honolulu star-bulletin (Online) 2326-1145 (DLC) 2013218511 (OCoLC)232117605"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:30.200Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220227/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["2021220226", "online resource", "2021220227", "2021220559", "2021220228", "904430143", "2767-8628", "2013218511", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Sunday bulletin"], "partof": ["evening bulletin (honolulu [oahu, hawaii]) 1895-1912 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "periodicals", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "electronic journals", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "Evening bulletin", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220227/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220249/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["kenyon, g. c.", "sheldon, j. g. m. (john g. m.)", "spencer, thomas p."], "date": "1891", "dates": ["[1891 TO 1895]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sat.-Sun.) Print began in May 1891; ceased in 1895. Editors: T.P. Spencer, G.C. Kenyon, J.G.M. Sheldon. Cf. Mookini, E.K. Hawaiian newspapers. Beginning with Feb. 1, 1894 issue, vol. numbering repeats from buke 1, helu 1. In Hawaiian. Issued simultaneously with daily bilingual (Hawaiian/English) ed. of the same title: Hawaii holomua. Vol. III, No. 143 (June 20, 1894); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Apr. 5, 2021). Vol. III, No. 176 (July 30, 1894) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Apr. 5, 2021)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:30.200Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220249/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["hawaiian"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["904431875", "2021220249", "online resource", "2767-8539", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Hawaii puka-la holomua"], "partof": ["hawaii holomua (honolulu) 1891-1895 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "periodicals", "hawaiians", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "pacific islander", "honolulu", "electronic journals", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "Hawaii holomua", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220249/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220534/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["irwin, e. p.,"], "date": "1910", "dates": ["[1910 TO 1910]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sunday) Print began with Vol. I, No. 1 (October 25, 1910); ceased with Vol. I, No. 13 (November 8, 1910). Editor: E.P. Irwin. Vol. I, No. 1 (October 25, 1910); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Sept. 29, 2021). Vol. I, No. 13 (November 8, 1910) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Sept. 29, 2021)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:12.813Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220534/", "image_url": [], "index": 9, "language": ["english"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["online resource", "2021220534", "701512893", "2770-2316", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the democrat (honolulu, t.h.) 1910-1910 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:02:22.050Z", "title": "The Democrat", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220534/"}], "next_resource": {"label": "Next Issue", "ur